code: import torch from transformers import BertForMaskedLM, BertTokenizerFast import pandas as pd from tqdm import tqdm import editdistance # Use faster tokenizer and smaller model for efficiency model_name = "bert-base-uncased" tokenizer = BertTokenizerFast.from_pretrained(model_name) model = BertForMaskedLM.from_pretrained(model_name) model.to("cuda") model.eval() def predict_missing_word(sentence): words = sentence.split() if len(words) < 2: return sentence # Generate all possible masked positions masked_sentences = [] positions = [] for i in range(1, len(words)): masked = words[:i] + ["[MASK]"] + words[i:] masked_sentences.append(" ".join(masked)) positions.append(i) if not masked_sentences: return sentence # Process all masks in one batch inputs = tokenizer( masked_sentences, padding=True, truncation=True, max_length=128, return_tensors="pt", ).to("cuda") with torch.no_grad(): outputs = model(**inputs) # Find best prediction for each mask position best_score = -float("inf") best_prediction = sentence mask_token_id = tokenizer.mask_token_id for idx, (logits, pos) in enumerate(zip(outputs.logits, positions)): mask_idx = (inputs.input_ids[idx] == mask_token_id).nonzero(as_tuple=True)[0] if mask_idx.numel() == 0: continue mask_idx = mask_idx[0] probs = torch.softmax(logits[mask_idx], dim=-1) top_token_id = probs.argmax() score = probs[top_token_id].item() if score > best_score: predicted_word = tokenizer.decode(top_token_id, skip_special_tokens=True) new_sentence = words[:pos] + [predicted_word] + words[pos:] best_score = score best_prediction = " ".join(new_sentence) return best_prediction # Validation using corrected file path val_size = 50 val_original = [] val_corrupted = [] with open("input/train_v2.txt", "r", encoding="utf-8") as f: for _ in range(1000): line = f.readline().strip() if not line: break words = line.split() if len(words) < 3: continue remove_pos = torch.randint(1, len(words) - 1, (1,)).item() corrupted = " ".join(words[:remove_pos] + words[remove_pos + 1 :]) val_original.append(line) val_corrupted.append(corrupted) if len(val_original) >= val_size: break val_preds = [predict_missing_word(s) for s in tqdm(val_corrupted)] mean_dist = ( sum(editdistance.eval(o, p) for o, p in zip(val_original, val_preds)) / val_size ) print(f"Validation Mean Levenshtein Distance: {mean_dist}") # Process test data in batches test_sentences = [] with open("input/test_v2.txt", "r", encoding="utf-8") as f: test_sentences = [line.strip() for line in f] submission = [] for idx, sent in tqdm(enumerate(test_sentences), total=len(test_sentences)): processed = predict_missing_word(sent) submission.append({"id": idx + 1, "sentence": processed}) pd.DataFrame(submission).to_csv("submission/submission.csv", index=False, quoting=1)
